    <h4><b>Arrests of NFL Players: 2001-2016</b></h4>

    <br>


    <h5><b>Introduction</b></h5>
    <p>The purpose of this project is to take a cursory look at arrest data of American National Football League players from 2001 to 2016.  Using publically available arrest data from an NFL arrest API, a handful of criminal behaviors, arrests over time, and arrests by Team were compared.  Findings indicate differences between frequency of occurrence by crimes and team.</p>



    <h5><b>Methodology and Data</b></h5>

    <p>This section will discuss the NFL Arrest API data, how the data was modified for analyses, and limitations to the data.</p>


    <h6><b><em>NFLArrest.com</em></b></h6>

    <p>The data for this project was courtesy of the nflarrest.com API, a website that tracks arrests of NFL players. This site collects data on every single arrest including the crime or crimes reported, the player arrested and the team they play for, and number of crimes per month.  These data include offenses occurring during and between January 31, 2001 to mid-2016.  While these data include a large quantity of detailed information, this project focused on the aggregate number of arrests and arrests by team.  This data is available only in a json format and was collected from the nflarrest.com website.</p>


